
Assignments on Date Functions

1.Implement the date functions of SQL.

2.Create the following table and perform the following queries.
Field	Datatype	Remark
EmpId	Varchar2(3)	Primary key, Should start with ‘E’
Ename	Varchar2(25)	Not Null
DOB	Date	Not Null
DOJ	Date	Not Null, Should later than DOB
Salary	Number(7)	Not Null, Should take only +ve value
Adhar	Number(12)	Unique, should always take 12 digit number
		
          
             create table Emp6( 
empid varchar(3) primary key, 
empname varchar(25) not null, 
dob date not null, 
doj date not null, 
salary number(7) not null, 
adhar number(12) unique, 
constraint chk check(empid like 'E%'), 
constraint chk1 check(doj> dob), 
constraint chk2 check(salary>0), 
constraint chk3 check(length(adhar)=12) 
)
insert into Emp6 values ('E01','VVV','12-jan-99','10-dec-17',10000,123456789888)
insert into Emp6 values ('E02','MMM','11-feb-01','09-nov-16',11000,124356789000)
insert into Emp6 values ('E03','PPP','10-mar-01','04-feb-16',12000,765432198763)
insert into Emp6 values ('E04','YYY','14-apr-03','03-mar-15',12500,368743999999)
insert into Emp6 values ('E05','XXX','15-apr-02','02-apr-15',13500,765534254364)


2.1List the employee details who joined on a particular date. 
select * from Emp6 where doj='02-APR-15'


2.2Write a query to list the employees with Hiredate in the format like February 22, 1991. 
select empname,to_char(doj,'month dd,yyyy') from Emp6

2.3Write a query to list the employees who joined before 2018.
select empname from Emp6 where doj<'01-jan-2018'

2.4Write a query to list the employees who joined in the month January.
select *from Emp6 where to_char(doj,'mon')='jan'

2.5Write a query to list the employees who have joined in the year 2019.
select *from Emp6 where to_char(doj,'yyyy')=2019

2.6Write a query to list the employee details according to the date of joining (recent joining should come first).
select *from Emp6 order by doj desc
